text: Proebstel is an unincorporated community in Clark County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Proebstel was established in 1886, and remained in operation until 1907. The community was named after John Proebstel, an early settler. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Clark County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Proebstel, Washington
